1:1 COMMENT "# io_readwrite.z -- write bytes to a file and read them back."
1:62 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# Exercises io.open, file.write, file.close, and file.read end-to-end."
3:71 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# Every fallible call returns `result(T, ioerror)`; this example"
4:65 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# handles ok arms and lets err arms fall through to a brief message."
5:69 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "#"
6:2 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# RAII: each result goes out of scope at the end of its block; the"
7:67 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# compiler-emitted destructor closes the fd on behalf of files that"
8:68 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# weren't closed explicitly."
9:29 EOL "\n"
